#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.74"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.74:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.74:0.2"
msgid "8. Gilānavagga"
msgstr "8. Sick"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.74:0.3"
msgid "74. Paṭhamagilānasutta"
msgstr "74. Sick (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.46"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn35.74:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn35.74:1.3"
msgid ""
"“amukasmiṃ, bhante, vihāre aññataro bhikkhu navo appaññāto ābādhiko dukkhito "
"bāḷhagilāno."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, in such and such a monastery there’s a mendicant who is junior and not "
"well-known. He’s sick, suffering, gravely ill."

msgctxt "sn35.74:1.4"
msgid ""
"Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "Please go to him out of compassion.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā navavādañca sutvā gilānavādañca, “appaññāto bhikkhū”ti iti "
"viditvā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha heard that the mendicant was junior and ill, understanding "
"that he was not well-known, he went to him."

msgctxt "sn35.74:2.2"
msgid "Addasā kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ."
msgstr "That mendicant saw the Buddha coming off in the distance"

#. VAR: samadhosi → samañcosi (bj) | samatesi (s1-3, km) | samañcopi (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.74:2.3"
msgid "Disvāna mañcake samadhosi."
msgstr "and tried to rise on his cot."

msgctxt "sn35.74:2.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to that monk:"

msgctxt "sn35.74:2.5"
msgid "“alaṃ, bhikkhu, mā tvaṃ mañcake samadhosi."
msgstr "“It’s all right, mendicant, don’t get up."

msgctxt "sn35.74:2.6"
msgid "Santimāni āsanāni paññattāni, tatthāhaṃ nisīdissāmī”ti."
msgstr "There are some seats spread out, I will sit there.”"

msgctxt "sn35.74:2.7"
msgid "Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane."
msgstr "He sat on the seat spread out"

msgctxt "sn35.74:2.8"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to the mendicant:"

msgctxt "sn35.74:2.9"
msgid ""
"“kacci te, bhikkhu, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyaṃ, kacci dukkhā vedanā "
"paṭikkamanti no abhikkamanti, paṭikkamosānaṃ paññāyati no abhikkamo”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“I hope you’re keeping well, mendicant; I hope you’re alright. I hope that "
"your pain is fading, not growing, that its fading is evident, not its "
"growing.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Na me, bhante, khamanīyaṃ, na yāpanīyaṃ, bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā "
"abhikkamanti no paṭikkamanti, abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati no paṭikkamo”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I’m not keeping well, I’m not alright. The pain is terrible and "
"growing, not fading; its growing is evident, not its fading.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:4.1"
msgid "“Kacci te, bhikkhu, na kiñci kukkuccaṃ, na koci vippaṭisāro”ti?"
msgstr "“I hope you don’t have any remorse or regret?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:5.1"
msgid "“Taggha me, bhante, anappakaṃ kukkuccaṃ, anappako vippaṭisāro”ti."
msgstr "“Indeed, sir, I have no little remorse and regret.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.47"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: taṃ → tvaṃ (bj, pts1) | te (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.74:6.1"
msgid "“Kacci pana taṃ, bhikkhu, attā sīlato upavadatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“I hope you have no reason to blame yourself when it comes to ethical "
"conduct?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: sīlato upavadatī”ti → no hetaṃ bhante (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.74:7.1"
msgid "“Na kho maṃ, bhante, attā sīlato upavadatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“No sir, I have no reason to blame myself when it comes to ethical conduct.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
#. VAR: atha kiñca → atha kismiñca (bj) | atha bhikkhu kismiñca (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.74:8.1"
msgid ""
"“No ce kira te, bhikkhu, attā sīlato upavadati, atha kiñca te kukkuccaṃ ko "
"ca vippaṭisāro”ti?"
msgstr "“In that case, mendicant, why do you have remorse and regret?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Na khvāhaṃ, bhante, sīlavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Because I understand that the Buddha has not taught the Dhamma merely for "
"the sake of ethical purity.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:10.1"
msgid ""
"“No ce kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, sīlavisuddhatthaṃ mayā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāsi, "
"atha kimatthaṃ carahi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mayā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāsī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“If that is so, what exactly do you understand to be the purpose of teaching "
"the Dhamma?”"

# For ragaviraga, compare AN 2.21.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:11.1"
msgid "“Rāgavirāgatthaṃ khvāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I understand that the Buddha has taught the Dhamma for the purpose of the "
"fading away of greed.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:12.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhu."
msgstr "“Good, good, mendicant!"

msgctxt "sn35.74:12.2"
msgid "Sādhu kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, rāgavirāgatthaṃ mayā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāsi."
msgstr ""
"It’s good that you understand that I’ve taught the Dhamma for the purpose of "
"the fading away of greed."

msgctxt "sn35.74:12.3"
msgid "Rāgavirāgattho hi, bhikkhu, mayā dhammo desito."
msgstr "For that is indeed the purpose."

msgctxt "sn35.74:12.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhikkhu, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicant? "

msgctxt "sn35.74:12.5"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:13.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:14.1"
msgid "“… pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.74:14.2"
msgid "Sotaṃ …"
msgstr "“Is the ear …"

msgctxt "sn35.74:14.3"
msgid "ghānaṃ …"
msgstr "nose …"

msgctxt "sn35.74:14.4"
msgid "jivhā …"
msgstr "tongue …"

msgctxt "sn35.74:14.5"
msgid "kāyo …"
msgstr "body …"

msgctxt "sn35.74:14.6"
msgid "mano nicco vā anicco vā”ti?"
msgstr "mind permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:15.1"
msgid "“Anicco, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:16.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:17.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:18.1"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to "
"be regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn35.74:18.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:19.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:20.1"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhu, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, "
"sotasmimpi nibbindati … pe … manasmimpi nibbindati."
msgstr ""
"“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, "
"ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind."

msgctxt "sn35.74:20.2"
msgid ""
"Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn35.74:20.3"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti … pe … nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended … there is no return to any state of "
"existence.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.74:21.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn35.74:21.2"
msgid "Attamano so bhikkhu bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandi."
msgstr "Satisfied, that mendicant was happy with what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn35.74:21.3"
msgid ""
"Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne tassa bhikkhuno virajaṃ vītamalaṃ "
"dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"And while this discourse was being spoken, the stainless, immaculate vision "
"of the Dhamma arose in that mendicant:"

msgctxt "sn35.74:21.4"
msgid "“yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman”ti."
msgstr "“Everything that has a beginning has an end.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.74:21.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
